Provably you should use `ThreadLocal.withInitial()`?

```java
class ContextHolder {

    private final static ThreadLocal&lt;String&gt; DATA =
                    ThreadLocal.withInitial(() -&gt; &quot;initial value&quot;);
    
}
```

It will initialize the thread local value once per thread.

[Java - Set the initial value for thread-local variable][1]


  [1]: http://www.java2s.com/example/java-book/set-the-initial-value-for-thread-local-variable.html

